Ring-opening Hydroformylation of a-Cyclopropylstyrene by HMn(C0)5, and Structure
of a Novel Mn2(CO)9(q1-Aldehyde) Complex
R. Morris Bullock,a* Brian J. Rappoli," Edward G. Samsel,a and Arnold L. Rheingoldb
a Department of Chemistry, Brookhaven National Laboratory,
Upton, New York 11973, U.S.A.
b Department of Chemistry, University of Delaware,
Newark, Delaware 19716, U.S.A.
An q1-aldehyde complex, Mn2(CO)9[Me(Ph)C=CHCH2CH2CHO], was isolated from the reaction of a-cyclopropyl-
styrene with wet HMn(C0)5; the crystal structure of this unusual compound confirmed the ql ( 0 ) bonding of the
aldehyde oxygen as an equatorial ligand on Mn2(CO)9.
Received, 27th September 1988;
Com. 8103796E
